# Environment Configuration

Create `.env` in the backend directory:

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/ai_news
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
JWT_SECRET_KEY=your-super-secret-key-change-this-in-production
CLAUDE_API_KEY=sk-...your-claude-key
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...your-openai-key  
PINECONE_API_KEY=...your-pinecone-key
PINECONE_ENVIRONMENT=us-west1-gcp
PINECONE_INDEX=ai-news
```

Create `.env.local` in the frontend directory:

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
```

## Getting API Keys

### Claude API (Anthropic)
- Go to: https://console.anthropic.com
- Sign up or login
- Create API key

### OpenAI API
- Go to: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
- Sign up or login  
- Create API key

### Pinecone Vector Database
- Go to: https://www.pinecone.io
- Sign up or login
- Create API key
- Choose environment (us-west1-gcp recommended for lower latency)

### PostgreSQL
- If running locally, use the credentials in docker-compose.yml
- If using cloud, update DATABASE_URL accordingly
